{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Twenty-eight years ago,\nI was a broken man."},{"time":4760,"text":"And you probably wouldn't be able\nto tell that if you met me."},{"time":8240,"text":"I had a good job at a well-respected\nacademic institution."},{"time":12840,"text":"I dressed well, of course."},{"time":15760,"text":"But my insides were rotting away."},{"time":18640,"text":"You see, I grew up in a family\nriddled with addiction,"},{"time":22640,"text":"and as a kid, I also struggled"},{"time":24124,"text":"with coming to terms\nwith my own sexuality."},{"time":26920,"text":"And even though I couldn't name it then,"},{"time":29280,"text":"growing up as a gay kid"},{"time":31320,"text":"just compounded my issues\nof isolation and insecurities."},{"time":36520,"text":"But drinking took all of that away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40840,"text":"Like many, I drank at an early age."},{"time":44840,"text":"I continued to drink\nmy way through college."},{"time":47840,"text":"And when I finally did come out\nin the early 1980s,"},{"time":50680,"text":"about the only places\nto meet other gay people,"},{"time":53520,"text":"to socialize,"},{"time":55520,"text":"to be yourself, were gay bars."},{"time":58360,"text":"And what do you do in gay bars?"},{"time":60480,"text":"You drink."},{"time":62080,"text":"And I did --"},{"time":63720,"text":"a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65760,"text":"My story is not unique."},{"time":67960,"text":"Like millions of Americans,\nmy disease progressed undiagnosed."},{"time":72400,"text":"It took me to people\nand places and things"},{"time":74400,"text":"that I never would have chosen."},{"time":77200,"text":"It wasn't until\nan intersection with the law"},{"time":80040,"text":"gave me an \"opportunity\" to get care,"},{"time":83880,"text":"that I began my journey of recovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"My journey of recovery\nhas been filled with love and with joy,"},{"time":91960,"text":"but it hasn't been without pain."},{"time":93960,"text":"Like many of you, I've lost too many\nfriends and family to this disease."},{"time":97960,"text":"I've heard too many\nheartbreaking stories"},{"time":99920,"text":"of people who've lost\nloved ones to addiction."},{"time":102760,"text":"And I've also lost\ncountless friends to HIV and AIDS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107160,"text":"Our current opioid epidemic\nand the AIDS epidemic"},{"time":110720,"text":"tragically have much in common."},{"time":114040,"text":"Right now, we are in the midst of one\nof the greatest health crises of our time."},{"time":119280,"text":"During 2014 alone, 28,000 people"},{"time":123640,"text":"died of drug overdoses associated\nwith prescription drugs and heroin."},{"time":130160,"text":"During the 1980s, scores of people\nwere dying from HIV and AIDS."},{"time":135800,"text":"Public officials ignored it."},{"time":138520,"text":"Some wouldn't even utter the words."},{"time":141800,"text":"They didn't want treatment."},{"time":144280,"text":"And tragically, there are many parallels\nwith our current epidemic."},{"time":148720,"text":"Some called it the gay plague."},{"time":151520,"text":"They called for quarantines."},{"time":154440,"text":"They wanted to separate\nthe innocent victims from the rest of us."},{"time":160120,"text":"I was afraid we were losing this battle"},{"time":162480,"text":"because people were\nblaming us for being sick."},{"time":166800,"text":"Public policy was being held hostage\nby stigma and fear,"},{"time":171880,"text":"and also held hostage"},{"time":173160,"text":"were compassion, care,\nresearch, recovery and treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179640,"text":"But we changed all that."},{"time":182480,"text":"Because out of the pain of those deaths,"},{"time":185080,"text":"we saw a social and political movement."},{"time":188800,"text":"AIDS galvanized us into action;"},{"time":192920,"text":"to stand up, to speak up and to act out."},{"time":198200,"text":"And it also galvanized\nthe LGBT movement."},{"time":202520,"text":"We knew we were\nin a battle for our lives"},{"time":204480,"text":"because silence equaled death,"},{"time":206960,"text":"but we changed,\nand we made things happen."},{"time":210760,"text":"And right now, we have the potential"},{"time":213080,"text":"to see the end of HIV/AIDS\nin our lifetime."},{"time":218480,"text":"These changes came in no small part"},{"time":221320,"text":"by the courageous, yet simple decision"},{"time":225160,"text":"for people to come out"},{"time":227440,"text":"to their neighbors,\nto their friends, to their families"},{"time":233480,"text":"and to their coworkers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236560,"text":"Years ago, I was a volunteer\nfor the Names Project."},{"time":240200,"text":"This was an effort started\nby Cleve Jones in San Francisco"},{"time":243600,"text":"to show that people who died of AIDS"},{"time":245600,"text":"had names"},{"time":247560,"text":"and faces and families"},{"time":251320,"text":"and people who loved them."},{"time":255120,"text":"I still recall unfolding\nthe AIDS memorial quilt"},{"time":260920,"text":"on the National Mall\non a brilliant day in October, 1988."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271440,"text":"So fast forward to 2015."},{"time":274480,"text":"The Supreme Court's decision to strike\ndown the ban on same-sex marriage."},{"time":279760,"text":"My husband, Dave, and I walk over\nto the steps of the Supreme Court"},{"time":282960,"text":"to celebrate that decision\nwith so many other people,"},{"time":285920,"text":"and I couldn't help but think\nhow far we came around LGBT rights"},{"time":291320,"text":"and yet how far we needed to go\naround issues of addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298120,"text":"When I was nominated\nby President Obama"},{"time":300000,"text":"to be his Director of Drug Policy,"},{"time":302200,"text":"I was very open about my recovery\nand about the fact that I was a gay man."},{"time":306720,"text":"And at no point during\nmy confirmation process --"},{"time":309080,"text":"at least that I know of --"},{"time":310640,"text":"did the fact that I was a gay man\ncome to bear on my candidacy"},{"time":314640,"text":"or my fitness to do this job."},{"time":317760,"text":"But my addiction did."},{"time":320680,"text":"At one point, a congressional staffer\nsaid that there was no way"},{"time":324160,"text":"that I was going to be confirmed\nby the United States Senate"},{"time":327040,"text":"because of my past,"},{"time":328640,"text":"despite the fact that I had been\nin recovery for over 20 years,"},{"time":332080,"text":"and despite the fact"},{"time":333320,"text":"that this job takes a little bit\nof knowledge around addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339640,"text":"So, you know, this is the stigma"},{"time":342600,"text":"that people with\nsubstance use disorders"},{"time":344680,"text":"face every single day,"},{"time":346880,"text":"and you know, I have to tell you"},{"time":348480,"text":"it's still why I'm more comfortable\ncoming out as a gay man"},{"time":351960,"text":"than I am as a person\nwith a history of addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355640,"text":"Nearly every family in America\nis affected by addiction."},{"time":359760,"text":"Yet, unfortunately, too often,\nit's not talked about openly and honestly."},{"time":366160,"text":"It's whispered about."},{"time":367840,"text":"It's met with derision and scorn."},{"time":371320,"text":"We hear these stories,\ntime and time again, on TV, online,"},{"time":376760,"text":"we hear it from public officials,\nand we hear it from family and friends."},{"time":381720,"text":"And those of us with an addiction,\nwe hear those voices,"},{"time":385560,"text":"and somehow we believe that we are\nless deserving of care and treatment."},{"time":391040,"text":"Today in the United States,\nonly one in nine people"},{"time":394440,"text":"get care and treatment for their disorder."},{"time":397000,"text":"One in nine."},{"time":398600,"text":"Think about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400600,"text":"Generally, people with other diseases\nget care and treatment."},{"time":403680,"text":"If you have cancer, you get treatment,"},{"time":405680,"text":"if you have diabetes, you get treatment."},{"time":407720,"text":"If you have a heart attack,"},{"time":409080,"text":"you get emergency services,\nand you get referred to care."},{"time":413200,"text":"But somehow people with addiction\nhave to wait for treatment"},{"time":416440,"text":"or often can't get when they need it."},{"time":419800,"text":"And left untreated, addiction\nhas significant, dire consequences."},{"time":424360,"text":"And for many people\nthat means death or incarceration."},{"time":429000,"text":"We've been down that road before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431400,"text":"For too long our country felt"},{"time":432840,"text":"like we could arrest our way\nout of this problem."},{"time":435880,"text":"But we know that we can't."},{"time":438680,"text":"Decades of scientific research has shown"},{"time":441080,"text":"that this is a medical issue --"},{"time":443240,"text":"that this is a chronic medical condition"},{"time":445840,"text":"that people inherit\nand that people develop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"So the Obama administration\nhas taken a different tack on drug policy."},{"time":454560,"text":"We've developed and implemented\na comprehensive plan"},{"time":457520,"text":"to expand prevention services,\ntreatment services,"},{"time":460920,"text":"early intervention and recovery support."},{"time":464800,"text":"We've pushed criminal justice reform."},{"time":467640,"text":"We've knocked down barriers\nto give people second chances."},{"time":470880,"text":"We see public health and public safety\nofficials working hand in hand"},{"time":474320,"text":"at the community level."},{"time":476480,"text":"We see police chiefs across the country\nguiding people to treatment"},{"time":479680,"text":"instead of jail and incarceration."},{"time":482400,"text":"We see law enforcement\nand other first responders"},{"time":485320,"text":"reversing overdoses with naloxone\nto give people a second chance for care."},{"time":491640,"text":"The Affordable Care Act\nis the biggest expansion"},{"time":494320,"text":"of substance use disorder\ntreatment in a generation,"},{"time":497600,"text":"and it also calls for the integration\nof treatment services within primary care."},{"time":504280,"text":"But fundamentally,\nall of this work is not enough."},{"time":508840,"text":"Unless we change the way\nthat we view people with addiction"},{"time":512880,"text":"in the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515400,"text":"Years ago when I finally\nunderstood that I had a problem"},{"time":519000,"text":"and I knew that I needed help,"},{"time":521159,"text":"I was too afraid to ask for it."},{"time":524320,"text":"I felt that people would think\nI was stupid, that I was weak-willed,"},{"time":529520,"text":"that I was morally flawed."},{"time":533880,"text":"But I talk about my recovery\nbecause I want to make change."},{"time":538240,"text":"I want us to see that we need to be open\nand candid about who we are"},{"time":544200,"text":"and what we can do."},{"time":546320,"text":"I am public about my own recovery"},{"time":548720,"text":"not to be self-congratulatory."},{"time":551440,"text":"I am open about my own recovery\nto change public opinion,"},{"time":555320,"text":"to change public policy"},{"time":557240,"text":"and to change the course of this epidemic\nand empower the millions of Americans"},{"time":561160,"text":"who struggle with this journey"},{"time":563040,"text":"to be open and candid\nabout who they are."},{"time":566640,"text":"People are more than their disease."},{"time":569880,"text":"And all of us have the opportunity\nto change public opinion"},{"time":573200,"text":"and to change public policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576000,"text":"All of us know someone\nwho has an addiction,"},{"time":579280,"text":"and all of us can do our part"},{"time":581240,"text":"to change how we view people\nwith addiction in the United States."},{"time":586400,"text":"So when you see\nsomeone with an addiction,"},{"time":588840,"text":"don't think of a drunk or a junkie\nor an addict or an abuser --"},{"time":595680,"text":"see a person;"},{"time":598040,"text":"offer them help;"},{"time":599560,"text":"give them kindness and compassion."},{"time":602360,"text":"And together, we can be part"},{"time":604600,"text":"of a growing movement\nin the United States"},{"time":606680,"text":"to change how we view\npeople with addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609480,"text":"Together we can change public policy."},{"time":612440,"text":"We can ensure that people\nget care when they need it,"},{"time":616360,"text":"just like any other disease."},{"time":619040,"text":"We can be part of a growing,\nunstoppable movement"},{"time":622760,"text":"to have millions of Americans\nenter recovery,"},{"time":625800,"text":"and put an end to this epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627920,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629160,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}